00:23:28,674 --> 00:23:32,684
And again, this was part of
the Scottish culture

481
00:23:33,345 --> 00:23:36,475
where the Highland Games were
mostly created so

482
00:23:37,016 --> 00:23:39,916
you could practice war arts
under the nose of the English

483
00:23:40,419 --> 00:23:41,999
without them actually knowing.

484
00:23:42,321 --> 00:23:45,071
So all the games
go back to that kind of thing

485
00:23:45,557 --> 00:23:47,197
versus how they are played today.

486
00:23:49,328 --> 00:23:51,228
Here we see the triplets
being chased by Maudie,

487
00:23:51,597 --> 00:23:53,587
which is going to be a setup
and a payoff for

488
00:23:53,966 --> 00:23:55,835
later on in the film in the third act.

489
00:23:57,169 --> 00:23:58,629
Fantastic atmosphere
in the background,

490
00:23:58,938 --> 00:24:01,218
just to set the depth of those Highlands.

491
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:03,510
-That is a Carnyx.
-Carnyx, yeah.

492
00:24:03,876 --> 00:24:06,506
Yeah. And that tongue actually moves.
There's a little wooden piece with it.

493
00:24:06,979 --> 00:24:09,529
Yeah, it was
an actual war horn they would use,

494
00:24:09,982 --> 00:24:12,032
usually shaped like a boar.

495
00:24:12,418 --> 00:24:16,287
And so we adapted it to make it a bear.
So it's thematically for our movie.

496
00:24:16,922 --> 00:24:19,702
But they would use that 'cause
it would rise up above the soldiers.

497
00:24:20,192 --> 00:24:23,002
Yeah, it would be
up above the attacking armies

498
00:24:23,495 --> 00:24:26,564
and scare the other army to death.

499
00:24:27,099 --> 00:24:28,908
That predates the bagpipe.

500
00:24:32,571 --> 00:24:36,031
The crowds in this movie
are spectacular.

501
00:24:36,608 --> 00:24:39,678
They're just amazing.
I mean, just the character design.

502
00:24:40,212 --> 00:24:42,962
I don't know how many different people
we actually had

503
00:24:43,449 --> 00:24:45,089
and different hair designs
and different clothes

504
00:24:45,417 --> 00:24:49,167
that they could inter-swap just to
make them this mass of individuals.

505
00:24:49,788 --> 00:24:52,368
It just really works fantastic.

506
00:24:53,993 --> 00:24:54,525
And just again setting up
character through action.

507
00:24:54,526 --> 00:24:56,106
And just again setting up
character through action.

508
00:24:56,428 --> 00:24:59,828
Every one of these archers has
a different way of shooting that bow.

509
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,640
And this guy is just hilarious.

510
00:25:02,901 --> 00:25:05,451
And his little groupie girls behind him.

511
00:25:08,574 --> 00:25:10,214
Long ago we had
a version of this where,

512
00:25:10,542 --> 00:25:12,151
before we had the lords' sons,

513
00:25:12,478 --> 00:25:14,118
there was a version of the games

514
00:25:14,446 --> 00:25:18,866
where Merida just didn't like this idea of
these guys playing for her at all.

515
00:25:19,585 --> 00:25:21,775
And so she just gets in there
and starts a brawl.

516
00:25:22,187 --> 00:25:23,996
-We actually had a haggis toss.
