00:26:47,973 --> 00:26:49,753
l also wanted to do this in slow motion

545
00:26:50,109 --> 00:26:54,799
to really just put the aspect of,
she is winning herself.

546
00:26:55,547 --> 00:26:59,447
And she has to beat them undoubtedly,
in no uncertain terms,

547
00:27:00,085 --> 00:27:03,565
that she is the best and so
you couldn't argue it away from her.

548
00:27:04,156 --> 00:27:05,495
So, I really wanted to slow it down.

549
00:27:05,791 --> 00:27:08,660
I had a lot more slow motion moments
in the sequence.

550
00:27:09,161 --> 00:27:11,531
And it stayed too long in Nick's terms.

551
00:27:11,964 --> 00:27:14,454
-We overstayed our welcome?
-That's correct.

552
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:16,100
But we really get to break down and see

553
00:27:16,368 --> 00:27:18,328
the archers' paradox
that happens with the bow.

554
00:27:18,704 --> 00:27:20,924
You guys can
look that up on Wikipedia.

555
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:22,600
But it actually occurs.

556
00:27:23,242 --> 00:27:24,262
The argument.

557
00:27:24,510 --> 00:27:26,910
This was a scene that we had
done really early on in the film.

558
00:27:27,346 --> 00:27:29,306
And it always remained as
the ultimate fight,

559
00:27:29,681 --> 00:27:31,461
the knock-down drag-out
between Mom and Merida here

