00:27:31,817 --> 00:27:33,747
that we really wanted to
kick off the rest of the film.

561
00:27:34,119 --> 00:27:36,259
Yeah, Emma Thompson worked
herself up into a froth

562
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:38,085
when she was doing this scene.
It was amazing,

563
00:27:38,390 --> 00:27:40,670
‘cause she actually had the stool
in the studio

564
00:27:41,093 --> 00:27:42,643
in her hands and her face turned red.

565
00:27:42,961 --> 00:27:45,421
And she had really gotten herself
into a state

566
00:27:45,864 --> 00:27:47,944
to get Mom's rage in this moment.

567
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:50,413
It's like all that bottled up rage

568
00:27:50,802 --> 00:27:52,992
at her daughter's misbehavior
is coming out.

569
00:27:53,405 --> 00:27:54,665
Well, there's something great
in this scene, too,

570
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:57,160
that they really go at each other here.

571
00:27:57,576 --> 00:28:01,616
But they both cross the line
and regret it.

572
00:28:02,281 --> 00:28:04,860
Merida chops that tapestry
and Mom burns that bow,

573
00:28:05,317 --> 00:28:08,977
but you quickly see that they
come down out of their tempers.

574
00:28:09,588 --> 00:28:13,947
Right. There's hypocrisy that's going on
in this scene for both characters.

575
00:28:14,660 --> 00:28:17,440
That they're both unwilling to yield,

576
00:28:17,930 --> 00:28:21,360
and, yeah, they cross the line in their
attempt to punish the other person.

577
00:28:21,934 --> 00:28:23,864
And it just all goes bad from there.

578
00:28:24,636 --> 00:28:27,946
Yeah, and Emma dialed up the intensity
even more so than she had before.

579
00:28:28,507 --> 00:28:30,497
And she adlibbed that line,

580
00:28:30,876 --> 00:28:32,836
"It'll be fire and sword
if it's not set right."

581
00:28:33,212 --> 00:28:36,372
We loved when our actors would
give us material like that

582
00:28:36,915 --> 00:28:38,225
that felt really authentic.

583
00:28:38,517 --> 00:28:40,657
I mean, Emma Thompson's
a writer in her own right.

584
00:28:41,053 --> 00:28:44,533
So, it was great to work with her
and get her suggestions

585
00:28:45,123 --> 00:28:46,873
and it was like
watching a private performance

586
00:28:47,226 --> 00:28:48,426
every time we're recording her.

587
00:28:48,694 --> 00:28:49,744
And Mom knew
she was wrong right away.

588
00:28:49,995 --> 00:28:50,844
Like a parent,

589
00:28:51,396 --> 00:28:52,626
sometimes you step over the line

590
00:28:52,898 --> 00:28:54,328
and realize you're acting like a kid.

591
00:28:54,633 --> 00:28:56,473
And she regrets it right away

592
00:28:56,835 --> 00:28:59,555
when she steps over
and hurts that precious bow.

593
00:29:00,038 --> 00:29:02,088
This is the same bow that Dad
gave her in the beginning of the movie.

594
00:29:02,474 --> 00:29:03,874
Merida, in this moment,
we always felt like

595
00:29:04,176 --> 00:29:05,755
she was a teenager that got into her car

596
00:29:06,078 --> 00:29:07,628
and drove out of the driveway
and took off.

597
00:29:07,946 --> 00:29:10,966
And she's just letting Angus
run wherever he wants.

598
00:29:11,483 --> 00:29:13,503
She's just along for the ride
and just wailing.

599
00:29:14,286 --> 00:29:16,066
And this scene here, the ring of stones,

600
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:20,081
we had debated for a long time
on how to introduce this location.

601
00:29:20,692 --> 00:29:22,062
There was even a time
earlier on in the film

602
00:29:22,361 --> 00:29:25,291
where Merida and her dad
had actually seen this spot before

603
00:29:25,797 --> 00:29:27,607
and now she's going to return to it.

604
00:29:27,966 --> 00:29:29,226
But ultimately we came down to,

605
00:29:29,501 --> 00:29:32,491
"Just let her visit the place
when she happens to go there."

606
00:29:33,005 --> 00:29:36,195
Right. These big standing stones
that are around in Scotland

607
00:29:36,742 --> 00:29:38,822
that were set up by the Picts
or who knows who

608
00:29:39,211 --> 00:29:42,611
and what their purpose was
is still in question.

609
00:29:43,215 --> 00:29:46,845
But there's ideas about fairy rings
and circle rings being magical.

610
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:50,232
And for our purposes in Brave
this circle ring is magical.

611
00:29:50,722 --> 00:29:53,762
It ends up being a type of portal
that we always return to.

612
00:29:54,293 --> 00:29:55,753
And Angus knows it and Angus...

613
00:29:56,061 --> 00:29:59,721
That animal sense is why
he won't cross into the circle,

614
00:30:00,332 --> 00:30:01,792
is that something is going to happen.

615
00:30:02,100 --> 00:30:05,320
He kind of understands that
on his animalistic level.

616
00:30:05,871 --> 00:30:07,511
We were inspired by
the Callanish stones

617
00:30:07,839 --> 00:30:10,009
which we saw on our research trip.

618
00:30:10,409 --> 00:30:13,569
But there's all kinds of stones like this
scattered around in Scotland.

619
00:30:14,112 --> 00:30:17,072
You could just find a strange stone
in someone's backyard.

620
00:30:17,582 --> 00:30:19,132
Right. Whether they were
stood up by giants, or...

621
00:30:19,451 --> 00:30:22,061
One of our guys
had a great idea, a theory

622
00:30:22,521 --> 00:30:25,301
that they were way markers
for navigating across land.

623
00:30:25,791 --> 00:30:26,811
That you'd be able to see them

624
00:30:27,059 --> 00:30:31,219
and they'd point you in a direction of
where the next stones were,

625
00:30:31,897 --> 00:30:33,506
or where the next town or village
or city was.

626
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:35,352
And I thought was
a really interesting idea.

627
00:30:35,667 --> 00:30:37,447
l hadn't heard that one before.

628
00:30:37,803 --> 00:30:41,753
But the wisps here are leading her
to her fate or a possible fate.

629
00:30:42,407 --> 00:30:43,547
And she follows them,

630
00:30:43,809 --> 00:30:45,829
like she followed them
at the beginning of the movie,

631
00:30:46,211 --> 00:30:49,081
which leads her to the Witch's cottage.

