00:30:51,249 --> 00:30:54,089
We know we're getting into
unchartered terrain in here,

634
00:30:55,020 --> 00:30:55,870
and that it's a little more threatening.

635
00:30:56,088 --> 00:30:58,168
A little bit more Snow White
to the forest here.

636
00:30:58,557 --> 00:31:01,957
Yeah, magical going from
the light side into the dark side.

637
00:31:02,527 --> 00:31:03,817
This ancient black house cottage.

638
00:31:04,096 --> 00:31:06,496
It looks like the cottages
that we saw in Scotland as well.

639
00:31:06,932 --> 00:31:07,832
Stone cottage with...

640
00:31:08,066 --> 00:31:10,876
Covered with like grass
and moss on top.

641
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:17,050
Now this scene was the very first scene
that we ever got approved

642
00:31:17,809 --> 00:31:19,509
to go into production on the film,

643
00:31:19,845 --> 00:31:21,155
but actually turned out to be

644
00:31:21,446 --> 00:31:26,485
the very last scene we actually
got finalized in making the film.

645
00:31:27,285 --> 00:31:30,565
Yeah, there was so many different
versions of who this Witch was.

646
00:31:31,123 --> 00:31:32,763
And how even Merida even entered

647
00:31:33,091 --> 00:31:35,700
or discovered
what was really going on in this set.

648
00:31:36,161 --> 00:31:39,201
Julie Walters does
a fantastic job with the voice.

649
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:41,901
And we went over a lot of ground,

650
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:48,010
really nailing down and getting specific
with who this character was.

651
00:31:48,907 --> 00:31:52,887
From a nice old lady to a maniac lady
to a ditzy lady.

652
00:31:53,545 --> 00:31:55,065
She tried it tons of different ways

653
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:57,630
before we finally
got the scene working right.

654
00:31:58,049 --> 00:32:00,269
And now she's just
kind of a proud salesman.

655
00:32:00,685 --> 00:32:04,315
This kindly old lady who just does art
in the back of her house,

656
00:32:04,923 --> 00:32:08,233
but is very excited about
the prospect of having a customer.

657
00:32:08,794 --> 00:32:12,014
At one point we had her as this
addled lunatic that had cabin fever.

658
00:32:12,564 --> 00:32:14,844
And when she'd see a wisp,
it was like a mouse in her kitchen

659
00:32:15,267 --> 00:32:17,107
and she'd just wail at it with her broom.

660
00:32:17,469 --> 00:32:20,929
We're really fighting
what everybody knows about witches.

661
00:32:21,506 --> 00:32:22,306
We've seen them so much
in films and in literature

662
00:32:22,307 --> 00:32:23,917
We've seen them so much
in films and in literature

663
00:32:24,242 --> 00:32:26,292
that they come with their own baggage.

664
00:32:26,678 --> 00:32:31,248
So how do we make it fresh and new
and super entertaining.

665
00:32:31,983 --> 00:32:33,243
The Crow character is unique

666
00:32:33,518 --> 00:32:36,358
in that we discovered along the way
of building the scene.

