00:33:39,451 --> 00:33:41,091
that we find out later is the same.

688
00:33:41,419 --> 00:33:43,669
But how do we
get those kinds of exposition

689
00:33:44,089 --> 00:33:46,168
that we absolutely need to have,

690
00:33:46,558 --> 00:33:48,578
and make it entertaining?

691
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:51,800
Yeah, there are a group of elements
floating around in the story,

692
00:33:52,297 --> 00:33:54,787
the first being Mom's story
about the ancient kingdom,

693
00:33:55,233 --> 00:33:57,133
and then you get
a second set of information

694
00:33:57,502 --> 00:33:59,841
when you're in here about the prince.

695
00:34:00,539 --> 00:34:03,559
And then it's not until the ruins
that you find out the full story.

696
00:34:04,075 --> 00:34:05,005
Right.

697
00:34:05,243 --> 00:34:06,993
We came up with this idea that

698
00:34:07,345 --> 00:34:09,395
when she walks in
it's a wood carver's shop

