And Merida fires an arrow
and makes a bull's-eye,

1785
01:25:33,061 --> 01:25:35,431
and then Mom picks up the bow
and splits her arrow.

1786
01:25:35,864 --> 01:25:37,353
And she says, "You didn't get
everything from your father."

1787
01:25:37,666 --> 01:25:39,686
-Yeah, we had that for a while.
-We had that for a while,

1788
01:25:40,068 --> 01:25:43,318
but ultimately it went back to
that it's this competing thing

1789
01:25:43,872 --> 01:25:45,622
and what are they
out there competing for?

1790
01:25:45,974 --> 01:25:47,524
Are they still competing for her hand?

1791
01:25:47,843 --> 01:25:49,952
And it was just kind of
the wrong resolution.

1792
01:25:50,345 --> 01:25:52,595
But that, again, it went back
into that comparison,

1793
01:25:53,015 --> 01:25:56,115
and the suitors were hanging around.
So it was just muddy.

1794
01:25:56,652 --> 01:25:59,672
It was a great moment,
but it was a can of worms

1795
01:26:00,188 --> 01:26:01,528
and it opened up all these questions.

1796
01:26:01,857 --> 01:26:03,467
So that doing it this way,

1797
01:26:03,792 --> 01:26:06,402
not having everything resolved,
it's resolved.

